      "content": "I understand your concern, but even a small amount can significantly increase the risk of side effects. Melatonin and zolpidem both work on the central nervous system to induce sleep, and combining them can lead to excessive sedation, impaired motor function, and other dangerous effects. It's crucial to follow your doctor's guidance and use these medications as prescribed. If you're struggling with sleep, consider alternative strategies or discuss other options with your doctor. Safety first!",
      "source": "target",
